The first time when I saw her being meek（谦卑） that she might attain height.
第一次 当他明明可以进取 却故作谦卑

The second time when I saw her limping（跛行） before the crippled(瘸腿的).
第二次 当他在一个瘸子面前 跛足而行

The third time when she was given to choose between the hard and the easy, and she chose the easy.
第三次 当他被给予了 简单和困难的选择时，他选择了简单

The fourth time when she committed a wrong（犯下错误）, and comforted herself that others also commit wrong.
第四次 当他犯下了错误，却自我安慰说 别人也会犯同样的错误

The fifth time when she forbore for weakness（容忍了自己的软弱）, and attributed her patience to strength（却自以为坚强）.
第五次 他容忍了自己的软弱，但却自以为坚强。

The sixth time when she despised（蔑视） the ugliness of a face, and knew not that it was one of her own masks.
第六次 他蔑视别人的臭脸，但是却不知道 那正是他自己的一张面具。

And the seventh time when she sang a song of praise（高唱颂歌）, and deemed it a virtue（美德）.
第七次 当他高唱赞歌，并以此为美德。